{"TopicId":214594,"ForumId":119,"TopicTitle":"Kerbals still speaking reversed Spanish?","CreatedByName":"OHara","CreatedById":162784,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-06T21:27:27Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"OHara","CreatedById":162784,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-06T21:27:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI remember KSP\u0027s advertising videos used Spanish phrases, with the recording tape reversed, for Kerbal speech.\u00A0 I convinced myself that KSP2\u0027s countdown is this same kind of reversed Spanish, but I\u0027m not sure about the other radio chatter.\u00A0 The sounds of language sound very different in reverse, not how one would pronounce the word spelled in reverse.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan any native speakers confirm?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there anything interesting in the radio chatter?\u003Cbr\u003E\n(I would not guess anything here could be a spoiler you could use a spoiler block if it is.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mutex","CreatedById":106937,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-06T21:37:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve read for KSP2 they write the Spanish words out backwards and then pronounce the result, recording it forwards.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kaa253","CreatedById":68628,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-07T00:31:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224253465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022214594\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678138658\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022106937\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mutex\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Mutex said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve read for KSP2 they write the Spanish words out backwards and then pronounce the result, recording it forwards.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf that\u0027s what they did then it works for me. During the countdown I hear certain numbers in Mandarin, Thai and French.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pthigrivi","CreatedById":105624,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-07T01:39:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224253465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022214594\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678138658\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022106937\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mutex\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Mutex said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve read for KSP2 they write the Spanish words out backwards and then pronounce the result, recording it forwards.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah this is what it sounds like to me. Hence \u0022O-ko\u0022 rather than \u0022O-cho\u0022. And yeah it\u0027s absolutely adorable.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dakota","CreatedById":225122,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-07T01:51:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan confirm, still speaking backwards Spanish\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:grin:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 loading=\u0022lazy\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/grin.png\u0022 title=\u0022:grin:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-07T03:34:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u